      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean you said there's debate, but some economists argue that the high benefits in certain areas are directly causing people to opt out of low-wage jobs. isn't it pretty clear that these safety nets create a ceiling where it's just not worth it to work more? can you find some data that backs up that specific connection?",
